research/history/logs/agent_round_0050.stdout.log:2132:research/history/logs/agent_round_0049.stdout.log:1802:research/history/logs/agent_round_0044.stdout.log:1516:research/history/logs/agent_round_0043.stdout.log:2490:`lowrank_expert_topk` already consumes `cfg.trunk_rank`, and cost estimates show `TRUNK_RANK=128` would move the promising r42 point from ~0.81x to ~0.44x total cost. The blocker is override wiring: AutoResearch does not currently whitelist `TRUNK_RANK` for this family, so the next useful move is a minimal wiring fix plus a first validation run relative to r42.
